description:
This is a 21 minute workout called 'Beginner Interval Treadmill Workout | 20 Minutes' from the channel Sunny Health & Fitness.
The workout falls under Cardio/Treadmill and Cardio/Running.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Treadmill for this workout.
The workout has a The Endorphin Wave and The Reboot Workout vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Welcome to this 20-Minute Beginner Interval Treadmill Workout, designed to kickstart your fitness journey. In this workout, certified trainer Sam Candler will guide you through a series of walk, jog, and run intervals, helping you find your comfort zone and push it just a little bit. Get ready to boost your cardiovascular endurance and burn calories in just 20 minutes!

Workout Length: 20 minutes
Workout Level: Beginner
Products Used: SF-T7917
Trainer: Sam Candler

00:00 Warm Up
Start your workout with a proper warm-up to prepare your body for the upcoming exercises.

1:04 Comfortable Walking Pace
Begin with a comfortable walking pace, allowing your body to gradually transition into the workout.

1:45 Jog Intervals 
Increase the intensity by incorporating short jogging intervals. Jog for 20 seconds, challenging your muscles and elevating your heart rate. Repeat this pattern twice.
